## Day 1 — Setting up Kubernetes locally

**Goal:** Install Minikube and run first K8s cluster

**What I learned so far:**
- Minikube runs a single-node K8s cluster locally
- It uses Docker as a driver — cluster runs inside Docker
- kubectl is the CLI to talk to K8s (already installed v1.34)
- Three things needed before starting: Docker Desktop, kubectl, and Minikube

**Prerequisites check:**
- Docker: ✅ v29.1.3
- kubectl: ✅ v1.34.1  
- Minikube: ✅Installed (brew install minikube) for Mac
